Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to
the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to
the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%mins}.

Meanwhile, trim the @Asparagus{100%grams} and cut into thirds. When the pasta has
~{2%mins} left, add the asparagus to the same pan for the remaining time.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with oil and
stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams} and pop them onto
a piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fold the foil, sealing on all sides to create a parcel. Pop onto one side of a
large #baking tray{}.

When the oven is hot, roast on the bottom shelf until softened, ~{15-20%mins}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

== Pesto Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add half the garlic and fry for ~{1%min}.

Add the @Fresh Pesto{32%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%grams},
@Creme Fraiche{150%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Stir together,
bring to the boil. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer the sauce until
piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper, then remove from the heat.

== Caprese Bruschetta ==

When the tomatoes have ~{5%mins} left, remove from the oven.

Halve the @Ciabatta{1} and lay onto the other side of your baking tray,
cut-side up. Spread over the remaining garlic and drizzle with the
@Olive Oil for the Garlic Bread{1%tbsp}.

Bake the garlic bread on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{5-6%mins}.

While everything cooks, drain and slice the @Mozzarella{1%ball} into 1cm rounds.

== Assembly ==

When everything has finished cooking, stir the cooked pasta and asparagus through
the pesto sauce. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Lay the slices of mozzarella onto the garlic bread and top with the roasted
tomatoes.

Drizzle over the @Balsamic Glaze{12%ml}.

Share your ultimate creamy pesto pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams} to finish.

Serve with your caprese bruschetta alongside. Enjoy!